headline.main: Roosevelt-Churchill Parley Held Off Newfoundland, Woman Says; Mrs. S.J. Wagstaff Tells of Hearing News on Radio From Germany While She Was in Labrador -- Site Is No Secret There

lead_paragraph: Mrs. Samuel J. Wagstaff of Babylon, L.I., and nearly everybody in Labrador and Newfoundland, it seems, are pretty sure of where President Roosevelt and Prime Minister Churchill met to draft their eight points, although that matter is still an official secret in the United States and England.
abstract: Mrs S J Wagstaff says Germans broadcast conf site as off Argentia, Nfld; Dr G S King suggests Knox learn how Germans obtained news
